1
00:00:01,253 --> 00:00:05,007
NARRATOR: <i>Previously on</i> Angel:
- Connor, we're having a baby.

2
00:00:05,253 --> 00:00:08,484
- We don't know if it's Cordy.
- Or what she's got baking in her oven.

3
00:00:08,653 --> 00:00:11,326
Evil and pregnant?
I'm guessing it ain't cookies.

4
00:00:11,573 --> 00:00:14,007
Took you long enough to figure it out.

5
00:00:14,333 --> 00:00:15,527
[GLASS BREAKING]

6
00:00:15,813 --> 00:00:17,132
ANGEL:
Connor, wait!

7
00:00:17,333 --> 00:00:18,766
Come on!

8
00:00:19,173 --> 00:00:23,325
Maybe there's another way. A way
to bring our baby into the world now.

9
00:00:23,493 --> 00:00:25,211
- How?
- I'll need some special things.

10
00:00:25,413 --> 00:00:27,005
[SOBBING]

11
00:00:27,213 --> 00:00:28,532
[BLOOD SPLATTERS]

12
00:00:31,093 --> 00:00:34,608
It's coming.
The beginning of a new world.

13
00:00:34,813 --> 00:00:36,132
She lied to you, Connor.

14
00:00:37,133 --> 00:00:38,885
I'm so sorry.

15
00:00:39,053 --> 00:00:41,009
[CORDELIA SCREAMS]

16
00:00:45,493 --> 00:00:46,812
[YELLS]

17
00:00:48,413 --> 00:00:50,244
Oh, my God.

18
00:00:53,053 --> 00:00:54,930
You're beautiful.

19
00:00:56,013 --> 00:00:57,287
Angel.

20
00:01:17,813 --> 00:01:20,281
- It's all so...
- Unworthy.

21
00:01:20,933 --> 00:01:22,207
- Wonderful.

22
00:01:26,133 --> 00:01:27,691
Cordelia.

23
00:01:31,813 --> 00:01:33,929
Thank you...

24
00:01:34,093 --> 00:01:36,687
...for protecting me and nourishing me.

25
00:01:37,213 --> 00:01:39,966
Your spirit has been my shelter.

26
00:01:40,173 --> 00:01:42,448
But you can rest peacefully now.

27
00:01:42,613 --> 00:01:44,331
I'm here.

28
00:01:44,493 --> 00:01:46,688
That's all she wanted.

29
00:01:46,853 --> 00:01:48,605
To give you life.

30
00:01:48,933 --> 00:01:52,642
And I can feel all of it.

31
00:01:53,453 --> 00:01:59,050
The cold floor, the air, this skin.

32
00:01:59,333 --> 00:02:01,085
Everything is perfect.

33
00:02:01,533 --> 00:02:03,012
No.

34
00:02:03,733 --> 00:02:05,052
It's not.

35
00:02:09,053 --> 00:02:11,362
I came here to kill you.

36
00:02:17,053 --> 00:02:19,328
I should be punished.

37
00:02:20,973 --> 00:02:22,247
WOMAN:
Angel...

38
00:02:22,853 --> 00:02:25,128
...I can feel your suffering.

39
00:02:27,373 --> 00:02:28,692
But now...

40
00:02:30,613 --> 00:02:33,491
...that suffering is going to end.

41
00:02:51,093 --> 00:02:55,405
Shiny Happy People

42
00:03:38,253 --> 00:03:41,006
I should have done this a long time ago.

43
00:03:41,173 --> 00:03:44,848
I don't know what I was thinking,
letting these books be all unorganized.

44
00:03:45,013 --> 00:03:47,288
LORNE: One does tend to let
the housekeeping slide...

45
00:03:47,453 --> 00:03:49,444
...during an apocalypta-lite.

46
00:03:50,213 --> 00:03:54,411
Hey, honey, all this to-and-fro,
it's making me edgier.

47
00:03:54,813 --> 00:03:57,168
- What's that?
- Oh, relax.

48
00:03:57,333 --> 00:03:59,767
It's just the buzz saw.
Nothing to get worked up over.

49
00:03:59,933 --> 00:04:01,525
It's Gunn and Wes in the basement.

50
00:04:01,693 --> 00:04:04,412
They're dismembering that
armor-plated demon, Skip.

51
00:04:04,573 --> 00:04:05,847
Oh, right.

52
00:04:06,013 --> 00:04:10,325
There's been a lot of dismembering
going on in the basement, if you ask me.

53
00:04:10,493 --> 00:04:13,724
- It's been a busy month.
- God, why did it have to be her?

54
00:04:15,253 --> 00:04:17,892
- I think you skipped a groove, darling.
- Cordelia.

55
00:04:18,053 --> 00:04:21,284
Why couldn't the Beastmaster have
chosen some horrible, evil person...

56
00:04:21,453 --> 00:04:22,772
...to be its vessel?

57
00:04:22,973 --> 00:04:24,964
Wouldn't be much in
the way of camouflage.

58
00:04:25,133 --> 00:04:26,407
He's been gone so long.

59
00:04:26,573 --> 00:04:29,610
You've shifted gender pronouns,
sweetheart. Not that I'm judging...

60
00:04:29,773 --> 00:04:31,889
Angel. Do you think he found them?

61
00:04:32,053 --> 00:04:34,613
- Them being...?
- Connor and Cordy.

62
00:04:35,813 --> 00:04:37,292
Well...

63
00:04:38,373 --> 00:04:40,841
Maybe he got there too late,
and she already had it.

64
00:04:41,013 --> 00:04:43,129
- And by "it," you must mean the...
- The baby...

65
00:04:43,293 --> 00:04:45,761
...or the hell spawn, or whatever it is.

66
00:04:46,893 --> 00:04:50,488
Skip said the Beastmaster was
using Cordelia to give birth to itself.

67
00:04:50,653 --> 00:04:54,009
What if Angel didn't get there
in time to stop it?

68
00:04:54,293 --> 00:04:57,285
Or worse, what if he did
get there in time?

69
00:04:58,253 --> 00:04:59,572
Do you think he'd actually...

70
00:05:01,013 --> 00:05:02,287
...you know?

71
00:05:02,893 --> 00:05:04,849
Dismember Mama?

72
00:05:10,733 --> 00:05:13,247
Would Angel really kill Cordelia?

73
00:05:14,133 --> 00:05:16,363
To save the world?

74
00:05:24,093 --> 00:05:25,572
Son of a bitch.

75
00:05:27,213 --> 00:05:30,125
Okay, not that I was expecting
a transition, but still...

76
00:05:30,333 --> 00:05:32,403
Drop it, junior.

77
00:05:32,573 --> 00:05:33,892
Fred, don't get too close.

78
00:05:34,293 --> 00:05:36,727
- Drop it?
- You heard me. Drop the knife.

79
00:05:36,893 --> 00:05:39,691
But you're always after me
to clean up after myself.

80
00:05:40,453 --> 00:05:41,772
I was just gonna put it away.

81
00:05:43,853 --> 00:05:47,766
Are you still evil-ish?
Because I'm confused.

82
00:05:47,933 --> 00:05:53,405
- Guys, it's okay. He's with me.
- Oh, my God, Cordelia.

83
00:05:53,573 --> 00:05:56,690
- She's not...
- No, she's not dead.

84
00:05:56,853 --> 00:06:00,129
She's just resting.
She's in a peaceful place.

85
00:06:00,293 --> 00:06:02,363
No, I meant...

86
00:06:02,533 --> 00:06:04,012
...she's not pregnant.

87
00:06:04,173 --> 00:06:06,562
Oh. No, not anymore.

88
00:06:06,773 --> 00:06:09,446
Then you were too late?
The thing was born?

89
00:06:09,613 --> 00:06:11,729
I'm guessing it wasn't a chubby
little cherub?

90
00:06:12,213 --> 00:06:14,852
- Not exactly.
- But you killed it. It's dead, right?

91
00:06:16,133 --> 00:06:18,522
Well, I tried.

92
00:06:19,253 --> 00:06:21,289
I was going to.

93
00:06:22,693 --> 00:06:23,967
I just...

94
00:06:25,413 --> 00:06:28,610
You gotta stop torturing yourself, Dad.

95
00:06:31,253 --> 00:06:33,289
He was like this all the way back
in the car.

96
00:06:33,453 --> 00:06:34,727
It escaped, then?

97
00:06:35,693 --> 00:06:36,967
Disappeared.

98
00:06:38,773 --> 00:06:40,570
Didn't even say goodbye.

99
00:06:40,733 --> 00:06:43,725
Is that, like, baby evil?

100
00:06:43,933 --> 00:06:45,764
I imagine we're not
talking about a baby.

101
00:06:45,933 --> 00:06:47,207
No.

102
00:06:47,373 --> 00:06:50,809
- Okay, so what are we dealing with?
- Eight legs? Three heads? Horns?

103
00:06:50,973 --> 00:06:52,645
- Hey!
- No offense.

104
00:06:52,813 --> 00:06:56,647
- Two legs. One head. No horns.
- Let me guess. Green?

105
00:06:56,813 --> 00:06:59,452
No. Kind of...

106
00:06:59,613 --> 00:07:01,251
...mocha.

107
00:07:03,573 --> 00:07:05,325
- We need to find her.
- Agreed.

108
00:07:05,493 --> 00:07:07,609
Hope it's easier
to kill than the Beast.

109
00:07:07,773 --> 00:07:09,923
Kill? No, no kill.

110
00:07:10,093 --> 00:07:12,209
- Since when?
- Since we've all been saved.

111
00:07:12,653 --> 00:07:15,326
Oh, well, that's crazy talk.

112
00:07:16,613 --> 00:07:19,207
- They don't understand.
- No.

113
00:07:20,773 --> 00:07:23,003
We don't want to kill her.

114
00:07:23,333 --> 00:07:24,971
We just...

115
00:07:25,253 --> 00:07:29,007
...want to find her
so we can worship her.

116
00:07:31,653 --> 00:07:33,006
That's all.

117
00:07:33,173 --> 00:07:35,403
She's amazing. You'll go nuts.

118
00:07:35,573 --> 00:07:39,691
- Yeah, that'll help us relate better.
ANGEL: When you meet her...

119
00:07:40,253 --> 00:07:41,925
...you'll understand.

120
00:07:42,853 --> 00:07:47,369
Angel, whatever you're feeling right
now, it's some form of enchantment.

121
00:07:48,173 --> 00:07:49,447
Yeah.

122
00:07:52,813 --> 00:07:54,292
It's a spell.

123
00:07:54,453 --> 00:07:55,727
Think.

124
00:07:56,253 --> 00:07:59,131
Even before its birth,
this thing controlled Cordelia...

125
00:07:59,293 --> 00:08:01,284
...caused her to do unspeakable things.

126
00:08:02,013 --> 00:08:03,605
It's evil.

127
00:08:04,373 --> 00:08:08,446
Remember the rain of fire?
Permanent midnight?

128
00:08:08,613 --> 00:08:12,208
- All the horrors done in its name?
WOMAN: Must be rectified.

129
00:08:17,453 --> 00:08:19,489
My God.

130
00:08:21,213 --> 00:08:23,329
People keep saying that.

131
00:08:23,813 --> 00:08:25,212
I'm just gonna...

132
00:08:26,133 --> 00:08:28,089
...do this.

133
00:08:30,293 --> 00:08:33,171
For so long, you've all been drowning.

134
00:08:34,053 --> 00:08:37,045
And the fighting and the pain.

135
00:08:40,653 --> 00:08:42,644
I'd like to help.

136
00:08:44,293 --> 00:08:46,488
If you'll have me.

137
00:08:48,053 --> 00:08:49,611
Tell us what to do.

138
00:08:51,213 --> 00:08:54,922
Eternal bliss. It suits her.

139
00:08:56,093 --> 00:08:58,448
FRED:
Cordelia must be so happy...

140
00:08:59,813 --> 00:09:02,281
...to be the one who brought you here.

141
00:09:02,453 --> 00:09:03,932
What an honor.

142
00:09:04,413 --> 00:09:06,051
I'm the one who's honored.

143
00:09:06,213 --> 00:09:08,408
By Cordelia...

144
00:09:09,093 --> 00:09:11,209
...and by all of you.

145
00:09:11,573 --> 00:09:15,009
I can't tell you how good it is
to be back.

146
00:09:15,213 --> 00:09:16,931
Back?

147
00:09:17,373 --> 00:09:19,682
- Then you've been here before?
WOMAN: Yes.

148
00:09:19,853 --> 00:09:22,731
In the beginning,
before the time of man.

149
00:09:22,893 --> 00:09:25,612
Great beings walked the Earth.

150
00:09:26,493 --> 00:09:29,451
Untold power emanated
from all quarters.

151
00:09:29,613 --> 00:09:33,003
The seeds of what would come
to be known as good and evil.

152
00:09:33,893 --> 00:09:37,010
But the shadows stretched
and became darkness...

153
00:09:37,173 --> 00:09:39,767
...and the malevolent
among us grew stronger.

154
00:09:39,933 --> 00:09:41,969
The Earth became a demon realm.

155
00:09:42,333 --> 00:09:45,086
Those of us who had
the will to resist...

156
00:09:45,253 --> 00:09:46,606
...left this place.

157
00:09:47,053 --> 00:09:49,123
But we remained ever watchful.

158
00:09:49,293 --> 00:09:52,126
You're a Power that was?

159
00:09:52,853 --> 00:09:56,482
But then something new emerged
from deep inside the Earth.

160
00:09:56,653 --> 00:09:59,645
- Neither demon nor god.
- Man.

161
00:10:00,613 --> 00:10:04,401
And it seemed for a time
that through this new race...

162
00:10:04,573 --> 00:10:07,610
...a balance might be restored.

163
00:10:07,773 --> 00:10:09,968
Guess we really let you down.

164
00:10:10,333 --> 00:10:11,732
But you didn't.

165
00:10:11,973 --> 00:10:14,533
It was we who failed you.

166
00:10:15,213 --> 00:10:17,966
We became little more than observers.

167
00:10:18,133 --> 00:10:21,170
I could no longer bear to just watch.

168
00:10:21,333 --> 00:10:22,971
All the suffering...

169
00:10:23,133 --> 00:10:25,601
...I had to find a way back.

170
00:10:25,773 --> 00:10:28,128
But first I needed a miracle.

171
00:10:28,893 --> 00:10:31,361
And so I arranged one.

172
00:10:34,173 --> 00:10:36,050
Through you, Angel.

173
00:10:36,213 --> 00:10:37,532
Through Darla.

174
00:10:37,853 --> 00:10:40,003
That is where my parentage began.

175
00:10:40,173 --> 00:10:44,451
Two vampires. Creatures once human,
corrupted by darkness.

176
00:10:44,613 --> 00:10:46,285
And you with a soul.

177
00:10:46,453 --> 00:10:48,523
A miracle already.

178
00:10:50,293 --> 00:10:52,648
- But how?
- Through Lorne.

179
00:10:52,813 --> 00:10:54,292
Huh?

180
00:10:54,453 --> 00:10:59,163
The day Lorne sent Angel
and human Darla into the trials...

181
00:10:59,333 --> 00:11:01,130
...to earn a new chance at life.

182
00:11:01,293 --> 00:11:03,932
- I failed.
WOMAN: No.

183
00:11:04,093 --> 00:11:07,005
You earned that life,
and there it is.

184
00:11:07,333 --> 00:11:13,169
All these events unfolded that I
might re-enter this physical plane.

185
00:11:13,373 --> 00:11:15,409
I know there's been chaos.

186
00:11:15,573 --> 00:11:19,202
All the events we've witnessed these
past months, all the madness...

187
00:11:19,893 --> 00:11:21,485
...it was birth pains.

188
00:11:22,293 --> 00:11:25,569
- But the storm has passed.
- And here comes the sun.

189
00:11:25,893 --> 00:11:29,442
And Cordelia. Will she wake up?

190
00:11:29,853 --> 00:11:34,369
If we take hold of the world,
strip away the thorns...

191
00:11:34,933 --> 00:11:38,369
...win the battle,
then, yes, I think she will.

192
00:11:38,533 --> 00:11:40,364
How do we do that?

193
00:11:40,533 --> 00:11:42,364
One evil at a time.

194
00:11:42,573 --> 00:11:45,133
Much damage has been done
in my name.

195
00:11:45,293 --> 00:11:49,332
There are demons,
forces of hate all over this city.

196
00:11:49,493 --> 00:11:51,370
We're going to destroy them.

197
00:11:52,333 --> 00:11:54,722
We're going to change the world.

198
00:11:54,893 --> 00:11:56,611
Finally.

199
00:12:03,453 --> 00:12:05,523
Oh! That ain't gonna work.

200
00:12:05,693 --> 00:12:10,448
Could have told you that.
Clean up my lane, jackass.

201
00:12:14,053 --> 00:12:16,203
"Let's go to L.A.," you said.

202
00:12:16,373 --> 00:12:18,603
"Sun's gone out," you said.

203
00:12:19,093 --> 00:12:20,924
"Gonna be the feast of the century."

204
00:12:21,613 --> 00:12:23,012
But the sun is back...

205
00:12:23,173 --> 00:12:26,085
...and here we are wasting
our time, bowling.

206
00:12:26,253 --> 00:12:28,892
I'm telling you, something big is coming.

207
00:12:29,053 --> 00:12:32,045
And when it gets here, we're
gonna be in prime position for...

208
00:12:32,213 --> 00:12:33,487
An ass-whupping?

209
00:12:58,293 --> 00:13:01,968
- Sit with me.
- Do you think we should?

210
00:13:04,013 --> 00:13:05,412
We have nothing to fear.

211
00:13:06,573 --> 00:13:08,006
Okay.

212
00:13:09,653 --> 00:13:12,167
Now, what are we going to call me?

213
00:13:13,413 --> 00:13:14,926
You don't have a name.

214
00:13:15,293 --> 00:13:16,692
No.

215
00:13:17,253 --> 00:13:19,323
You should have a name.

216
00:13:19,693 --> 00:13:20,967
Yes.

217
00:13:21,893 --> 00:13:23,565
I don't know.

218
00:13:23,733 --> 00:13:28,761
I can't imagine one word,
you know, summing you up.

219
00:13:28,933 --> 00:13:32,562
I mean, you're a superior being.
Shouldn't you...?

220
00:13:33,533 --> 00:13:35,728
Don't you want
to choose it yourself?

221
00:13:36,093 --> 00:13:38,891
No one born to this Earth
can choose their own name.

222
00:13:39,053 --> 00:13:41,567
They're named
by those who love them.

223
00:13:41,933 --> 00:13:44,652
There are some rules
even I must follow.

224
00:13:48,533 --> 00:13:51,331
I'm so sorry. It's all my fault.

225
00:13:51,533 --> 00:13:55,924
I'll be fine. You tried to caution me.
I should have listened.

226
00:14:02,253 --> 00:14:04,926
ANGEL:
Hey, you hurt her, you scum!

227
00:14:18,333 --> 00:14:19,652
[WOMAN SCREAMS]

228
00:14:22,053 --> 00:14:23,327
Dad!

229
00:14:29,933 --> 00:14:31,207
MAN:
Over there.

230
00:14:32,573 --> 00:14:36,964
It's all right. It's over.
You're safe now.

231
00:14:37,133 --> 00:14:38,805
What?

232
00:14:39,013 --> 00:14:40,332
Oh...

233
00:14:41,973 --> 00:14:44,123
Everyone, please stand up.

234
00:14:44,293 --> 00:14:48,571
If you wish to honor me,
honor each other. We are all one.

235
00:14:48,733 --> 00:14:50,883
You're hurt.

236
00:14:55,013 --> 00:14:57,243
I'll be all right.

237
00:14:57,693 --> 00:14:59,888
Everything will be all right.

238
00:15:00,053 --> 00:15:05,411
All my life, so empty.
That's over now, isn't it?

239
00:15:05,573 --> 00:15:08,610
Yes, Margaret, it's over.

240
00:15:09,813 --> 00:15:11,087
I know you.

241
00:15:11,693 --> 00:15:12,967
I know you all.

242
00:15:13,133 --> 00:15:16,648
I've come here for you,
to bring you the gift of peace.

243
00:15:16,813 --> 00:15:20,203
You will be freed from
the pains you've suffered.

244
00:15:20,373 --> 00:15:25,163
The world will change forever, and you
will know the power of my love.

245
00:15:25,333 --> 00:15:28,928
The chaos will fade
and harmony will reign.

246
00:15:29,093 --> 00:15:30,685
Monster.

247
00:15:32,253 --> 00:15:34,084
It has to die!

248
00:15:51,253 --> 00:15:53,926
Angel, that's enough.

249
00:15:58,413 --> 00:16:00,404
[MAN SOBBING]

250
00:16:00,613 --> 00:16:02,524
Don't you see it?

251
00:16:05,173 --> 00:16:06,492
No.

252
00:16:07,453 --> 00:16:09,683
No, don't touch me!

253
00:16:11,973 --> 00:16:13,645
WOMAN:
Poor thing.

254
00:16:17,053 --> 00:16:20,090
- Wesley.
- I'll call an ambulance.

255
00:16:21,533 --> 00:16:23,364
All of you...

256
00:16:23,573 --> 00:16:27,202
...so loving, so strong.

257
00:16:27,893 --> 00:16:33,331
How can I ask you to understand
that a man like this...

258
00:16:33,893 --> 00:16:38,409
...so full of fear, anger, so alone...

259
00:16:38,573 --> 00:16:40,564
