511
00:33:54,853 --> 00:33:57,162
Okay, that's just eerie.

512
00:33:57,653 --> 00:34:00,850
It's Angel. They're probably
wondering where I am.

513
00:34:01,013 --> 00:34:03,368
- You have to do it.
- I have to go.

514
00:34:03,533 --> 00:34:05,683
Thank you.
I'm sorry to have disturbed you.

515
00:34:05,853 --> 00:34:08,890
Don't trust her. Don't trust anyone!

516
00:34:09,253 --> 00:34:10,572
[LAUGHING]

517
00:34:10,773 --> 00:34:12,729
GIRL:
I've never seen you like this.

518
00:34:12,893 --> 00:34:17,011
I'm telling you, you have
to meet her. Come on.

519
00:34:17,173 --> 00:34:20,449
LORNE: We are just excited head over
tea kettle about this entire event.

520
00:34:20,613 --> 00:34:24,401
I just can't even believe... Hey,
hey, hey, pumpkin, where you been?

521
00:34:24,573 --> 00:34:27,451
Out. What happened?

522
00:34:27,613 --> 00:34:30,173
She went for a walk.
It was like <i>A Hard Day's Night.</i>

523
00:34:30,333 --> 00:34:32,563
Everybody followed her back.
Isn't it fabulous?

524
00:34:32,733 --> 00:34:35,691
Oh, hey. Excuse me, darling.

525
00:34:38,693 --> 00:34:42,208
Can you believe this? What is it?

526
00:34:42,373 --> 00:34:45,126
I need you.

527
00:34:49,413 --> 00:34:51,643
If I told you something...

528
00:34:51,933 --> 00:34:54,652
...you know, that maybe
you didn't want to know even...

529
00:34:55,773 --> 00:34:57,092
...you'd trust me, right?

530
00:34:57,253 --> 00:34:59,369
Of course.

531
00:35:00,053 --> 00:35:01,327
I...

532
00:35:02,013 --> 00:35:04,208
I went to see that man
from the restaurant.

533
00:35:04,373 --> 00:35:07,126
- The one who...
- The attacker? Why?

534
00:35:07,573 --> 00:35:10,167
That's what I wanted to know,
why he would do that.

535
00:35:12,973 --> 00:35:14,292
Wesley...

536
00:35:15,093 --> 00:35:17,402
...he saw something.

537
00:35:20,613 --> 00:35:22,763
We both saw something.

538
00:35:23,093 --> 00:35:26,085
I needed to know if it
was the same something.

539
00:35:26,973 --> 00:35:29,965
- And?
- It was.

540
00:35:32,173 --> 00:35:36,803
Wesley, I know you're going
to find this hard to accept, but...

541
00:35:37,013 --> 00:35:39,004
[SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY]

542
00:35:42,453 --> 00:35:44,728
Rotting flesh?

543
00:35:45,133 --> 00:35:46,885
Really?

544
00:35:48,253 --> 00:35:50,369
You don't believe me.

545
00:35:52,093 --> 00:35:54,402
If you say you saw it, I believe you.

546
00:35:55,893 --> 00:35:58,009
He told me not to tell anyone.

547
00:35:58,173 --> 00:36:02,132
- But I knew if I came to you...
- You did the right thing.

548
00:36:02,333 --> 00:36:04,324
[CLAPPING]

549
00:36:13,253 --> 00:36:15,244
You'll help me?

550
00:36:16,933 --> 00:36:18,889
Of course I'll help you. Wait here.

551
00:36:27,013 --> 00:36:29,004
[SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY]

552
00:37:03,933 --> 00:37:05,207
I'm sorry.

553
00:37:25,333 --> 00:37:26,607
LORNE:
Fred!

554
00:37:26,893 --> 00:37:28,167
Are you crazy?

555
00:37:28,933 --> 00:37:30,844
What? Fred!

556
00:37:32,013 --> 00:37:34,447
- Don't come near me!
- Put down the knife.

557
00:37:34,613 --> 00:37:35,887
- I'll kill him!
- You don't...

558
00:37:36,093 --> 00:37:38,084
- I'll kill him.
- Easy, kiddo.

559
00:37:38,293 --> 00:37:39,806
There's nowhere you can go, Fred.

560
00:37:40,853 --> 00:37:42,844
My love will follow you everywhere.

561
00:37:44,573 --> 00:37:45,847
LORNE:
Hey!

562
00:37:47,133 --> 00:37:48,566
WOMAN:
Let her go.

563
00:37:49,133 --> 00:37:53,888
Now is not the time.
We are all gathered here in peace.

564
00:37:55,133 --> 00:37:57,567
Let's not let her
take that away from us.

565
00:38:37,733 --> 00:38:40,247
I can't believe Fred's evil.

566
00:38:40,493 --> 00:38:41,767
GUNN:
Should've seen it coming.

567
00:38:41,933 --> 00:38:47,053
Nothing like a homicidal maniac
to put a damper on a spiritual gathering.

568
00:38:47,213 --> 00:38:50,762
WOMAN: What they saw tonight,
it's not what I would have wanted.

569
00:38:51,293 --> 00:38:55,571
But now they all understand the reality
of what hatred can do to a person.

570
00:38:55,733 --> 00:38:57,007
ANGEL:
The reality is...

571
00:38:58,453 --> 00:39:01,923
...we need to find Fred.
- Thank you, Angel.

572
00:39:02,093 --> 00:39:04,448
This scent, it soothes me.

573
00:39:04,733 --> 00:39:07,452
We leave now, Connor and I
can probably still track her.

574
00:39:07,613 --> 00:39:09,365
I know you're all in pain.

575
00:39:09,533 --> 00:39:12,570
- You trusted Fred, and she betrayed you.
GUNN: Forget us.

576
00:39:13,093 --> 00:39:14,367
She tried to kill you.

577
00:39:14,533 --> 00:39:17,172
And the sadness
that brings me is immeasurable.

578
00:39:17,813 --> 00:39:20,532
I should've just
let her cut my head off.

579
00:39:21,253 --> 00:39:22,572
My species...

580
00:39:22,733 --> 00:39:24,166
...decapitation loophole.

581
00:39:24,333 --> 00:39:26,972
Still might have stabbed you,
let you bleed to death.

582
00:39:28,333 --> 00:39:30,449
Why didn't I see it?

583
00:39:31,413 --> 00:39:33,722
Angel, none of us did.

584
00:39:34,893 --> 00:39:36,724
You can't blame yourself.

585
00:39:36,893 --> 00:39:39,487
She was acting weird earlier.

586
00:39:39,653 --> 00:39:42,451
I just thought it was Fred...

587
00:39:42,973 --> 00:39:44,691
...being Fred.

588
00:39:45,533 --> 00:39:48,047
That man at the hospital...

589
00:39:48,813 --> 00:39:51,168
I'm still shocked
she would go to see him.

590
00:39:51,333 --> 00:39:54,131
Once he had her there, he
must have monkeyed with her brain.

591
00:39:54,293 --> 00:39:57,763
Maybe he made her do it,
with magic or something.

592
00:39:59,453 --> 00:40:01,728
I doubt even Fred understands...

593
00:40:01,893 --> 00:40:06,045
...why she's so determined to destroy
everything we're trying to create...

594
00:40:06,213 --> 00:40:08,443
...which makes
her even more dangerous.

595
00:40:08,853 --> 00:40:10,764
We have to kill her.

596
00:40:14,053 --> 00:40:15,327
There's no other way.

597
00:40:15,493 --> 00:40:17,848
As long as she's out there,
she's a threat.

598
00:40:18,013 --> 00:40:19,571
It may come to that.

599
00:40:20,133 --> 00:40:22,488
But first, we have to try to help her.

600
00:40:22,693 --> 00:40:25,571
Get to the root of the hatred
that's infected her heart.

601
00:40:25,733 --> 00:40:27,246
The only way
is to bring her home.

602
00:40:27,413 --> 00:40:28,732
- Let's go.
WOMAN: No.

603
00:40:29,053 --> 00:40:33,888
We'll find Fred, but not tonight.
Tomorrow will be easier than today.

604
00:40:34,293 --> 00:40:35,965
We'll have eyes everywhere.

605
00:40:40,053 --> 00:40:41,452
WAITER:
Here you go.

606
00:40:42,653 --> 00:40:44,803
Looks like you
just lost your best friend.

607
00:40:44,973 --> 00:40:46,326
All of them.

608
00:40:46,653 --> 00:40:50,407
- I never thought...
- Yeah, well, that's life in the big city.

609
00:40:51,893 --> 00:40:54,407
<i>Welcome back.</i>
<i>Chef Arnold Michske will join us later...</i>

610
00:40:54,573 --> 00:40:58,168
<i>... but right now we have the most</i>
<i>amazing surprise.</i>

611
00:40:58,333 --> 00:41:01,291
<i>Please join me in welcoming</i>
<i>a very special visitor...</i>

612
00:41:01,453 --> 00:41:04,763
<i>...Jasmine!</i>
JASMINE: <i>Good morning, Los Angeles.</i>

613
00:41:05,693 --> 00:41:08,810
<i>Thank you for inviting me.</i>
<i>This is a special day.</i>

614
00:41:09,093 --> 00:41:12,449
REPORTER: <i>We want to know everything</i>
<i>about you. Start at the beginning.</i>

615
00:41:12,653 --> 00:41:17,044
JASMINE: <i>Trish, in the beginning,</i>
<i>before the time of man...</i>

616
00:41:17,213 --> 00:41:19,488
<i>... great beings walked the Earth.</i>

617
00:41:19,653 --> 00:41:22,725
<i>Untold power emanated</i>
<i>from all quarters...</i>

618
00:41:22,893 --> 00:41:27,011
<i>... the seeds of what would</i>
<i>come to be known as good and evil.</i>

619
00:41:27,173 --> 00:41:32,372
<i>Yet there was a balance.</i>
<i>The shadows stretched...</i>

